sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Proxy as rest-proxy<br/>8008/TCP HTTP(S)
    participant Marshaler as Custom Marshaler<br/>(JSON ↔ Protobuf)
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh gRPC<br/>8033/TCP gRPC

    Note over Client,ModelMesh: Flow 1: REST Inference Request

    Client->>Proxy: POST /v2/models/{name}/infer<br/>Content-Type: application/json<br/>Optional TLS
    Proxy->>Marshaler: Parse JSON request body<br/>Flatten multi-dim arrays<br/>Base64 decode BYTES tensors
    Marshaler->>ModelMesh: ModelInfer RPC<br/>Protobuf InferRequest<br/>Optional TLS
    ModelMesh-->>Marshaler: InferResponse (protobuf)
    Marshaler-->>Proxy: Transform to JSON<br/>Reshape tensor data<br/>Base64 encode BYTES
    Proxy-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>JSON inference response

    Note over Client,ModelMesh: Flow 2: Model Metadata Request

    Client->>Proxy: GET /v2/models/{name}<br/>Optional TLS
    Proxy->>ModelMesh: ModelMetadata RPC<br/>Optional TLS
    ModelMesh-->>Proxy: ModelMetadataResponse
    Proxy-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>JSON model metadata

    Note over Client,ModelMesh: Flow 3: Versioned Model Inference

    Client->>Proxy: POST /v2/models/{name}/versions/{ver}/infer<br/>Optional TLS
    Proxy->>Marshaler: Parse JSON + version routing
    Marshaler->>ModelMesh: ModelInfer RPC (versioned)<br/>Optional TLS
    ModelMesh-->>Marshaler: InferResponse
    Marshaler-->>Proxy: JSON transformation
    Proxy-->>Client: 200 OK<br/>JSON inference response
